    'name' => 'service_orchestrator',
    'description' => 'Call two different live services in one pass and join their results into a consolidated report. Currently supports: \'name_demographics\' (calls nationalize.io + agify.io to predict nationality and age from a name), and \'topic_overview\' (calls Wikipedia summary + GitHub repo count for a topic). All network calls use PHP streams with independent timeouts. Never throws — all errors returned as structured data. Composition across two independent API domains.',
    'parameters' => 
    array (
      'type' => 'object',
